<paragraph id="9D6829590420FFB2FF18F92FFD2E92AD" blockId="4.[166,794,1779,2008]" pageId="4" pageNumber="99">
<emphasis id="AFA3F54B0420FFB2FF18F92FFF0A927E" box="[197,255,1779,1803]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="99">Head</emphasis>
in profile higher than long, with postfrons much longer than face; face rather short and broad, with only slightly raised median elevation, thus concave in profile; height of cheek c. 0.15–0.22 of height of eye. Antennal segment 3 tapered to subacute apex; arista almost bare, except for trace of minute pubescence near base. Prelabrum moderately large and deep, slightly receding below; palpus moderately large, setulose, broadly rounded apically.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="9D6829590420FFB3FCB8F92FFEE691B5" blockId="4.[839,1467,1779,2008]" lastBlockId="5.[121,749,987,1861]" lastPageId="5" lastPageNumber="100" pageId="4" pageNumber="99">
<emphasis id="AFA3F54B0420FFB2FCB8F92FFC47927E" box="[869,946,1779,1803]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="99">Thorax</emphasis>
elongate; humeral callus and mesoscutum very extensively haired; in female only, humeral callus with tuft of slightly longer black setulae behind humeral bristle, these undifferentiated in male; scutellum shorter than semicircle in dorsal view, with hairs rather long and generally distributed, but not dense; mesopleuron with numerous long hairs, mainly on posterior part; sternopleuron extensively haired. Fore femur with a series of long, fine posteroventral bristles, without differentiated dorsal bristles; other femora without distinct bristles; mid tibia with single large terminal ventral spur and several much smaller ones; legs otherwise without well developed armature. Wing as in 
<figureCitation id="05EC35DC0421FFB3FDFEFBEFFD9C913F" box="[547,617,1074,1099]" captionStart="Figures 4, 5" captionStartId="4.[310,387,1693,1715]" captionTargetBox="[186,1467,151,1678]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[167,1467,151,1679]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="Figures 4, 5. Microepicausta fenestra sp. nov., holotype male. (4) head and part of thorax. (5) right wing." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3838128" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3838128/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="100">Fig. 5</figureCitation>
; first costal cell, much of second costal cell, basal part of first basal cell, almost entire second basal and anal cells bare; alula bare; most of rest of wing membrane almost uniformly microtrichose.
</paragraph>
<caption id="C9A879D10421FFB3FFA4FCEEFEE696ED" ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3838130" ID-Zenodo-Dep="3838130" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3838130/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="100" startId="5.[121,198,818,840]" targetBox="[125,1417,160,785]" targetPageId="5">
<paragraph id="9D6829590421FFB3FFA4FCEEFEE696ED" blockId="5.[121,1421,818,920]" pageId="5" pageNumber="100">
<emphasis id="AFA3F54B0421FFB3FFA4FCEEFF059632" bold="true" box="[121,240,818,840]" pageId="5" pageNumber="100">Figures 6, 7</emphasis>
. 
<taxonomicName id="5AD752DA0421FFB3FF20FCEFFE139632" authority="Mcalpine, 2019" authorityName="Mcalpine" authorityYear="2019" box="[253,486,818,840]" class="Insecta" family="Platystomatidae" genus="Microepicausta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="100" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fenestra" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="AFA3F54B0421FFB3FF20FCEFFE139632" box="[253,486,818,840]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="100">
<taxonomicName id="5AD752DA0421FFB3FF20FCEFFE66963D" box="[253,403,819,840]" class="Insecta" family="Platystomatidae" genus="Microepicausta" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="100" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Microepicausta</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicName id="5AD752DA0421FFB3FE44FCEEFE139632" box="[409,486,818,839]" pageId="5" pageNumber="100" rank="species" species="fenestra" status="sp. nov.">fenestra</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="B49048300421FFB3FE31FCEFFDCC963D" box="[492,569,819,840]" pageId="5" pageNumber="100" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
, Musgrave, Qld. Details of male postabdomen. 
<emphasis id="AFA3F54B0421FFB3FBD9FCEEFBD59632" box="[1028,1056,818,839]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="100">(6)</emphasis>
Right cercus and surstyli. Scale = 0.1 mm. 
<emphasis id="AFA3F54B0421FFB3FF77FC91FF329617" box="[170,199,845,866]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="100">(7)</emphasis>
Aedeagus and associated structures. Scale = 0.3 mm. 
<emphasis id="AFA3F54B0421FFB3FD13FC91FD139617" box="[718,742,845,866]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="100">aa</emphasis>
, aedeagal apodeme; 
<emphasis id="AFA3F54B0421FFB3FC72FC91FC319617" box="[943,964,845,866]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="100">as</emphasis>
, aedeagal sheath; 
<emphasis id="AFA3F54B0421FFB3FBA9FC91FB759617" box="[1140,1152,845,866]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="100">b</emphasis>
, bulb of aedeagus; 
<emphasis id="AFA3F54B0421FFB3FAE1FC91FABD9617" box="[1340,1352,845,866]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="100">g</emphasis>
, glans; 
<emphasis id="AFA3F54B0421FFB3FFA4FCB4FF6F9608" box="[121,154,872,893]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="100">mw</emphasis>
, membranous wing of stipe; 
<emphasis id="AFA3F54B0421FFB3FE62FCB4FE229608" box="[447,471,872,893]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="100">pa</emphasis>
, process of aedeagal apodeme (paired); 
<emphasis id="AFA3F54B0421FFB3FCB5FCB4FC759608" box="[872,896,872,893]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="100">pg</emphasis>
, preglans; 
<emphasis id="AFA3F54B0421FFB3FC32FCB4FC0A9608" box="[1007,1023,872,893]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="100">st</emphasis>
, stipe; 
<emphasis id="AFA3F54B0421FFB3FB97FCBBFBA29609" box="[1098,1111,871,892]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="100">tf</emphasis>
, terminal filament; 
<emphasis id="AFA3F54B0421FFB3FAC1FCB4FADA9608" box="[1308,1327,872,893]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="100">tp</emphasis>
, terminal process of bulb.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph id="9D6829590421FFB3FF4AFB19FD1893E0" blockId="5.[121,749,987,1861]" pageId="5" pageNumber="100">
<emphasis id="AFA3F54B0421FFB3FF4AFB19FF0891A8" box="[151,253,1221,1245]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="100">Abdomen</emphasis>
. Preabdomen and female postabdomen with the general characters of the genus. 
<emphasis id="AFA3F54B0421FFB3FDCEFB3FFD10918E" box="[531,741,1251,1275]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="100">Male postabdomen</emphasis>
: anterior and posterior surstyli and cercus of similar length and prominence; outer (anterior) surstylus with single long terminal setula, its concave posterolateral surface with fine, dense, plush-like pubescence; inner surstylus without apparent surface armature, with attenuated basal articulation; cercus with numerous long setulae, on posterior surface with long, dense, erect pubescence; membranous aedeagal sheath (containing aedeagal apodeme) elongate, but not prominently projecting (at least in 
<typeStatus id="426C97FB0421FFB3FE29FA37FDD79376" box="[500,546,1515,1539]" pageId="5" pageNumber="100">type</typeStatus>
material); stipe of aedeagus distally with transparent membranous wing, which does not extend on to the otherwise slightly differentiated preglans; terminal bulb of glans compact and sclerotized, bearing an elongate, tapering process; terminal filament c. 2.4× as long as glans, simple, not much tapering distally.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="9D6829590421FFB3FF4AF947FD5C93BA" blockId="5.[121,749,987,1861]" pageId="5" pageNumber="100">
<emphasis id="AFA3F54B0421FFB3FF4AF947FE8D93C6" box="[151,376,1691,1715]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="100">Female postabdomen</emphasis>
: aculeus broader than in 
<taxonomicName id="5AD752DA0421FFB3FDA7F947FD1893C6" authorityName="Hendel, Bronte" authorityYear="1914" box="[634,749,1691,1715]" class="Insecta" family="Platystomatidae" genus="Microepicausta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="100" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="gracilis">
<emphasis id="AFA3F54B0421FFB3FDA7F947FD1893C6" box="[634,749,1691,1715]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="100">M. gracilis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="5AD752DA0421FFB3FF7BF965FEFF93A5" authorityName="Mcalpine" authorityYear="2019" box="[166,266,1720,1744]" class="Insecta" family="Platystomatidae" genus="Microepicausta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="100" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="wirthi">
<emphasis id="AFA3F54B0421FFB3FF7BF965FEFF93A5" box="[166,266,1720,1744]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="100">M. wirthi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, not tapering distally, rounded at apex.
</paragraph>
